notes: aajer-today's, daaderma-in day, telangana-telangane, ma che - is in

english: He felt the presence of Goddess Jagadamba.
banjara: Voon votthe Jagadamba devi che ju anubhav vi
notes: Voon-him, votthe-there, Jagadamba devi- Jagadamba godess, che ju-presence, anubhav vi-felt so

english: Also known as Goddess Mariamma Yaadi.
banjara: voonaz Devi mariamma yaadi ken bhi kach
notes: voonaz-her, Devi-godess, mariamma-mariamma, yaadi-mother, ken-meant, bhi-also, kach-said

english: He wished to offer her something.
banjara: voone, vu devi ne kai thoi chadavnu ken lago
notes: voone-him, vu-that, devi ne-to godesses, kai thoi-something, chadavnu-offer/give, ken lago- felt so

banjara: panan vor kan kaai vetto koni.
notes: panan-but, vor-him, kan-near, kaai-what ever, vetto-present/possess, koni-not

english: So he took mud and wheat.
banjara: tho haatherma dhud an gahu leedho
notes: tho-then, haatherma-in hands, dhud-mud, an-and, gahu-wheat, leedho-took

english: With pure devotion, he prepared sheera from mud.
banjara: voor bhakthi thi, dhud eethi sheera banayo
notes: voor-his, bhakthi-devotion, thi-with, dhud-mudd, eethi-with, sheera-sheera/sweet, banayo-prepared,cooked,made
